Just another day at 5k mmr. I pick the renowed windranger and say I want mid. Blue picked sf and also wants mid. I go safelane. We have an AM. I became support at minute 4. No couriers and wards just the strength of our skills and hearts. Seven minutes into the game I got flamed. Ten minutes into the game sf died three times. I rotate top. I gank. I died. I got flamed. "Time to get serious" is what I said. Thirty minutes into the game our carry lost hope and afk at base. My CM is out of control. Sf is feeding. The perfect time. Finished my aghs/daedalus. I thrive in a 1v9 situation. Odds are stacked I lose my composure. My heart beats faster with every kill. I die multiple times before realizing my true fate. I am windranger. I powershoot to victory. My teammates flame me. I mute them. I windrun. I bkb. I kill. Everything up to this point is a mere act. Two man shackles that baffles their minds. I kill. Enemy WW glimmer capes to safety. I powershoot. I kill. Not once have I doubted my ability. Couriers are everywhere. Fools. I am windranger. The racks melt at my focus fire. No buyback on the enemy team. I unmute to see what the fools have to say. "You're doing it wr". I muted them again. The enemy ancient never stood a chance. A grin appears on my face while typing "gg". I don't complain. I don't flame. I am windranger. The game ends.
